How to run MVP v1 locally

This project is available as a runnable local artifact.

Requirements

Before running the project, make sure you have installed:

* Docker
* Docker Compose
* Python 3

1. Clone the repository

git clone <repository-link>
cd SWP-AromaType

2. Start backend and database

From the project root folder, run:

docker compose up --build

This command starts:

* Go backend API on port 8080
* PostgreSQL database on port 5432

The backend automatically applies database migrations and creates the default admin user.

Backend health check:

http://localhost:8080/health

Swagger / API documentation:

http://localhost:8080/docs

3. Start frontend

Open a second terminal window and run:

cd frontend
python3 -m http.server 5173

Then open the frontend in browser:

http://localhost:5173/#quiz

The local frontend uses the backend API at:

http://localhost:8080

4. Admin access

Default local admin account:

Email: admin@aromatype.local
Password: local-admin-password

MVP v1 access point

The MVP v1 can be run locally using Docker Compose and the static frontend server.

Local frontend:

http://localhost:5173/#intro

